##CDC: Before the new Crown Epidemic, "we were so close. "

The day-to-day work of migrant workers at the grass-roots level, picture from Jinan Daily

By Ye Shuizhong

Edited by Chen Xiaoxue

●     　●  　   ●

Lu Feng (not his real name) returned home for the first time after a month and a half of continuous work after the outbreak of NCP was largely under control. "from when I was on call years ago until recently, when some people started going to and from work, there was no day or night, the schedule was disrupted, I often went out in the middle of the night to transfer, my nerves were high, and now I feel obviously out of sorts. "

Lu Feng is a county in the eastern part of the country CDC grassroots staff. Since the outbreak of the new crown disease, its jurisdiction has many imported cases in Wuhan, together with the imported cases infected local personnel, a total of 50 to 60 confirmed patients. The daily work of the local grassroots Centers for Disease Control and Prevention keeps them busy, and the new outbreak of pneumonia has doubled their work pressure in a short period of time.

At present, there are 3,500 centers for Disease Control and prevention at all levels in China, from the national level to the local level, divided into four levels (national, provincial, municipal and county centers) . There are 190,000 people like Lu Feng from the local centers for Disease Control and Prevention. After the outbreak of the new crown, as many as five million people from Hubei or Wuhan were scattered across the country, where they went, who was at low risk and who was at high risk, who has close contact with people who are suspected to be infected or have been diagnosed, and so much of the epidemiological work has fallen to grassroots migrant workers like Lu Feng.

However, before the outbreak of NCP, the local CDC was not taken seriously. In 2019, the health system was overhauled, and many centers were dismantled and restaffed. "We were ready to be withdrawn at any time and merged into other units or set up new units, but we didn't expect such a big epidemic. We were almost out of business, " Lu said.

In addition to the early stage of the epidemic, the National Center for Disease Control (CDC) because "why not early sounded the alarm" , "in the early study of the epidemic why speak of limited human-to-human transmission" , has become the focus of public opinion. And in the epidemic prevention and control and epidemiological investigation of the grass-roots disease control personnel, almost in the public "disappeared. ". In fact, they have been on the front lines, acting as disease "scouts" .

Epidemic Prevention and control is a race against time

In the epidemic period, the flow of work may appear at any time, and the field flow of the end of the need to be as soon as 24 hours to report the investigation. "reports are written for hours at a time, and staying up all night is the norm, " Lu said, "The prevention and control of the epidemic is time-grabbing, heavy work and lack of manpower, so we have to make use of the night time. It is very common for the staff of the whole unit to stay up late, and the CDC leadership basically stayed up late during the epidemic. "

The CDC is still lit up in the middle of the night on Jan. 30, in this photo released from Nantong

The so-called epidemic survey is the abbreviation of epidemiological investigation. It refers to the disease control personnel who go to the scene of epidemic situation to carry out investigation, communicate with patients and ask about their exposure, exposure, activity track and medical treatment before and after the onset of the disease, to look for clues about the source of infection, route of transmission and close contacts.

Most of the people infected in Lufeng's district came from Wuhan, and even the local cases came from close contact with people who had returned home from Wuhan. "these cases are all related to Wuhan. After all the returnees from Wuhan and their close contacts have been checked, all patients who have relevant symptoms and are positive for the new coronavirus nucleic acid test have been collected and treated, and no new cases have emerged, " he said, "At present, the focus of our prevention and control is on imported cases from abroad, " Lu said.

At the beginning of the epidemic, the action was "passive" 

As early as the end of 2019, there are media reports of unexplained pneumonia, as the local CDC front-line staff will not ignore this information. Lu's Center for Disease Control has been monitoring the outbreak since December. Although prepared, everything seems very passive: the CDC's long-standing role problem, so they can only be notified by their superiors to act.

"although we are concerned about the new outbreak of pneumonia, there are no cases in our jurisdiction, no notification from our superiors, and we can only stand by, " Lu said. The so-called war preparations, but also mainly information collection and material reserves, as well as carry out the corresponding publicity and training.

Why have you been on standby? Lu Feng also put forward his view: "The independence of disease control is very poor, because disease control is a sub-institutions of the Health Commission, Health Commission is a government department, long-established inertia and law-abiding, so the pace of regional disease control work is basically consistent with the local government. "

For grassroots disease control workers, even without a new outbreak, they are mostly on the front line all year round, usually dealing with a variety of epidemic, probably most of the public and media unknown. According to Lu, there are many departments under the CDC, only one of which is responsible for infectious disease surveillance. As soon as the medical institutions report, they should carry out epidemiological investigation and corresponding disposal at the first opportunity.

In addition to the day-to-day work of the CDC, the management of patients with severe mental disorders in the district is also undertaken by the CDC, "A lot of people think it's incredible how this work is related to the disease control and prevention, " Lu said. "We don't understand it, but maybe we can't find a more professional organization to take on these jobs, so let the CDC take on them. ".

On January 20, Zhong Nanshan suggested that there had been human to human transmission of NCP, and on the same day, the National Health Council included NCP AS A category B infectious disease and took measures to prevent and control it, at the same time, the new crown pneumonia will be included in the regulation of Quarantine Infectious Disease Management. At this time, Lu Feng's disease control center began to deal with the new crown pneumonia epidemic. Its local government immediately set up an epidemic prevention and control office. "We basically mobilized after the meeting at the provincial, City and district levels held on January 21, " Lu Feng said, "The epidemic prevention office is set up in the local health committee and is led by the main leaders of the local administrative bodies, including the leaders of the Centers for Disease Control and prevention at the municipal and district levels. "

Subsequently, the local prevention and control office began to issue a series of documents and guiding programs, continuously convening township and township authorities to carry out corresponding publicity work throughout the region; after that, a mapping and registration exercise was carried out for all returnees from Wuhan and Hubei, gradually close down all public places of business in areas under their jurisdiction, and the CDC has also sent personnel to carry out epidemic prevention and control, as well as disinfection and guidance work for public places such as supermarkets that have not been closed for the protection of people's livelihood, and requires all medical and health units to do a good job of protection, regulating the opening of fever clinic.

At this time, the grass-roots disease control staff work more busy, in addition to the regular information collection, material reserves, personnel training and public education, but also increased the epidemiological investigation, elimination, blockade, epidemic research and other work. "We needed to be on call at work and couldn't go home, " Lu recalled. Since all restaurants were closed during the outbreak, meals for staff on duty became a problem, but their unit solved the problem.

During the outbreak, Lu and his colleagues focused all their efforts on combating the disease, as routine work at the local CDC stopped short of involving patients'lives. Lu Feng said that the outbreak of grass-roots Disease Control is basically all staff on duty, all involved. "At the county level, we usually have between 50 and 100 people, and our unit is also short-staffed, so we have to borrow people from other agencies. "

The "scouts" of the epidemic

In response to the new crown pneumonia epidemic, local disease control, government and hospital how to cooperate with each other and division of Labor, Lu Feng what is their main work? Lu Feng said that the local centers for Disease Control and Prevention are "scouts, " taking the initiative to attack, giving advice to the government, reporting timely clues related to cases, managing the crowds in close contact with cases as soon as possible, carrying out elimination and killing, and opening the way for the entry of the follow-up forces, the local government is like the "general" , is the battlefield commander, the leader, overall planning, the hospital is like the "soldiers" , take care of cases and treatment, they participate in the fight against the epidemic team is of course the largest.

Epidemic Disease Control personnel at the grass-roots level on the spot to carry out the flow. Image courtesy of Nantong

When a suspected case appears in the area under their jurisdiction, the medical institution will report it to the CDC, and then CDC personnel will enter the ward at the first time to communicate with the patient, to obtain the basic information of the patient, the onset of disease, the course of diagnosis and treatment and clinical manifestations, the 14-day residence and travel history of the patient before the onset of disease, the history of suspicious exposure, the situation of contacts and other relevant information, as well as to carry out throat swab sampling work.

When this is done, they need to complete the patient's investigation report and evaluation within 24 hours in order to make recommendations for the next step of the epidemic prevention and control work. "The whole process of a patient lasts almost a day and the workload is huge, which is the most dangerous part of the disease control work, because most suspected patients are likely to be diagnosed eventually, and if we don't have protection in place or have an accident in the course of a few hours with an infected patient, there is a high risk of infection, " Lu said.

Especially in the early epidemic, the lack of a comprehensive understanding of the virus, how to do their own protection, there is no reference index. "intellectual" asked Lufeng if he was worried about being infected, he said, "have been worried about being infected, so have not seen his family, have been sleeping in the unit.

Fortunately, none of the staff at Lu's Center for Disease Control and Prevention had new pneumonia. "But if the virus were stronger, there would be, a strong virus that could penetrate the secondary shield, and there would be casualties, and we would certainly be the first to die. ". Lu quipped.

There are also many unforgettable moments in the process of Liudao. "Most of the patients were classified as suspicious or even diagnosed after many people feel very depressed, and even when they heard the news, they suddenly fainted, there are still others flat do not matter, what kind of, but it must be mainly pessimistic, there was a woman who had just given birth to a child, that test positive, immediately cried, said my child just came out, can not later without a mother. All we could do was try to comfort him."

The grassroots Centers for Disease Control and prevention are struggling,
"almost changed. "

The grassroots Centers for Disease Control and prevention are struggling,

"almost changed. "

Grass-roots Disease Control Staff Work Complex, pressure, the corresponding human and material resources are not in place, so the turnover rate is very high. In fact, this has to do with the CDC's continued marginalization and neglect in recent years.

In 2018, Shenyang overhauled its centers for Disease Control and Prevention

In 2018, the Shenyang Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Shenyang Health Supervision Institute and other units were integrated into the Shenyang Center for Health Services and administrative law enforcement, which is an institution affiliated to the Municipal Health and Family Planning Commission. In 2019, the health system pushed ahead with reforms that led to the abolition of the Centers for Disease Control and prevention in many parts of the country and the shunting of staff.

"We had been ready to be withdrawn at any time, merged into other units or set up new units, but we did not expect such a large epidemic, how to change the next step, we do not know, we almost changed it. ". Lu Feng said.

And in 2003, "SARS" , the National CDC system at all levels of continuous improvement, investment is also increasing. But since then, the reform of the CDC system has not only stagnated, the CDC has also been increasingly marginalized, the direct result is that the CDC is not only low status, not valued, investment has also declined significantly. According to a recent report in the Chinese Journal of Epidemiology by the Expert Group on the prevention and control of pneumonia of the COVID-19 of the Chinese Society for Preventive Medicine, in 2014 the National "Special Task Fund for Public Health" was allocated 529 million yuan, by 2019, that figure had fallen to 450 million, down 14.9 percent from a year earlier.

The panel also believes that the CDC's reforms have been in decline in recent years. In 2009, a new round of health care system reform was launched, ignoring the importance of public health. The performance-based pay reform implemented by the CDC eventually evolved into a new round of rice-and-beans, which seriously dampened the enthusiasm of disease control personnel, leading to a massive loss of professional talent. In April 2017, three fees including the "preventive medical examination fees" charged by the CDC as a public welfare institution were also cancelled. Since then, the grassroots CDC has no source of income at all, relying solely on local government funding, however, most of the region's financial security is not in place, the operation of the organization is difficult.

Zhong Nanshan has previously appealed to the media, the CDC's low status, poor independence, which makes it difficult for them in the first time to spread the sound of the epidemic study. In fact, the domestic disease control system still exists high turnover rate, difficult to attract talent and other issues.

"My school has always ranked among the top in public health subjects in the country, but very few of my classmates are involved in disease control. Only about 10 percent of my classmates in this year's graduating class are involved in the disease control system. Some of my classmates have gone into business after graduation, and some of my classmates have gone to work as city management officers, " Lu said, to retain people, we should not only enhance the status of CDC, but also "should improve the qualification of preventive medicine, improve the disease control and prevention system, improve the income level of disease control institutions. "
